bar_index â‡¨ ğ‘¥.description: Current bar index. Numbering is zero-based, index of the first bar is 0. | TYPE series int

timeframe.period â‡¨ ğ‘¥.description: A string representation of the chart's timeframe. The returned string's format is '[<quantity>][<units>]', where <quantity> and <units> are in some cases absent. <quantity> is the number of units, but it is absent if that number is 1. <unit> is 'S' for seconds, 'D' for days, 'W' for weeks, 'M' for months, but it is absent for minutes. No <unit> exists for hours. The variable will return: '10S' for 10 seconds, '60' for 60 minutes, 'D' for one day, '2W' for two weeks, '3M' for one quarter. Can be used as an argument with any function containing a `timeframe` parameter. | TYPE simple string
